SIMPLE: outflank
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outflank
<hw>Out*flank"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>To go beyond, or be superior to, on the flank; to
pass around or turn the flank or flanks of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>To outmaneuver in a
competition; to bypass a competitor's main defenses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outflatter</ent>⟦br⟧
